16:13.305 --> 16:14.306
Mm-hmm.

16:15.224 --> 16:19.561
I'm gonna be talking to them
about… me coming out.

16:25.985 --> 16:28.153
Oh my God, I'm so proud of you.

16:28.737 --> 16:30.114
-Yeah.
-Are you okay?

16:30.197 --> 16:31.949
I'm good. It's been a lot,

16:32.032 --> 16:34.702
just because…
I don't think a lot of people understand.

16:34.785 --> 16:37.579
I've been watching it
and just kind of waiting.

16:37.663 --> 16:38.706
-So, you know?
-Really?

16:38.789 --> 16:40.082
Yeah.

16:40.165 --> 16:43.127
Like a friend knows you,
and I'm very happy for you,

16:43.210 --> 16:46.630
even though there's a tear
gonna come down my face.

16:46.714 --> 16:48.799
But… I get it now.

16:48.882 --> 16:52.678
Like, it's all kind of making
a lot more sense, so…

16:52.761 --> 16:55.097
-Now you know my weirdness in high school.
-Well…

16:55.180 --> 16:57.725
-That was always questionable.

16:57.808 --> 16:59.101
All jokes aside,

16:59.810 --> 17:01.353
it's the real you, so…

17:01.437 --> 17:02.271
I know.

17:03.188 --> 17:06.150
-I mean, I feel good, I'm like…
-Sorry. I don't mean to cry.

17:06.233 --> 17:10.362
No. Like, I'm emotional. I'm happy.
I'm nervous. I'm scared.

17:10.446 --> 17:11.989
If you haven't been open about it,

17:12.072 --> 17:15.659
it's not gonna be something that just
comes out naturally all the time, so…

17:15.743 --> 17:17.578
Yeah. Right.

17:18.495 --> 17:19.329
Yeah.

17:19.413 --> 17:23.125
Feel like my biggest defense mechanism
is I would overcompensate.

17:23.208 --> 17:26.754
The captain of the football team dating
the captain of the cheerleading squad.

17:26.837 --> 17:28.172
-Like your typical…
-Yeah.

17:28.881 --> 17:29.715
All that.

17:29.798 --> 17:34.678
Like you kind of always had yourself
in this picture perfect world, and…

17:34.762 --> 17:35.846
Yeah.

17:35.929 --> 17:37.681
…it wasn't your truth, so…

17:41.977 --> 17:44.021
I didn't want to be gay.

17:44.104 --> 17:49.151
And the main voices in my head were
telling me, "You'll get through this."

17:49.777 --> 17:53.781
"Maybe it will just take
one really good girl to change you."

17:53.864 --> 17:56.450
And… that was Cassie.

17:57.451 --> 18:02.247
Everyone saw that first rose ceremony
as just another rose ceremony,

18:02.331 --> 18:05.250
but for me, it was so much more than that.

18:05.334 --> 18:08.420
I felt myself becoming
more of a straight man.

18:09.463 --> 18:12.216
Everyone saw that hometown date
on the beach

18:12.716 --> 18:14.551
and the connection that we had.

18:14.635 --> 18:18.097
But I felt like I found somebody
who could change me.

18:19.139 --> 18:22.101
The night that Cassie
was leaving me on The Bachelor…

18:22.184 --> 18:23.811
I'm not, like, in love.

18:24.394 --> 18:26.396
I don't know if I can get there with you.

18:26.480 --> 18:28.982
…there was a big part of me
that was thinking,

18:29.066 --> 18:30.484
"If I can't get there with you,

18:31.068 --> 18:33.570
then I definitely can't
with any other woman."

18:33.654 --> 18:34.655
After The Bachelor,

18:34.738 --> 18:38.283
our relationship was up and down,
and eventually we broke up,

18:38.951 --> 18:40.661
and I started to spiral.

18:40.744 --> 18:42.371
Four months
after their breakup,

18:42.454 --> 18:44.748
Randolph petitioned the courts
for a restraining order,

18:44.832 --> 18:46.708
claiming he put
a tracking device on her car.

18:46.792 --> 18:48.293
I was fucked up.

18:48.377 --> 18:51.839
I was suppressing my sexuality so hard.

18:51.922 --> 18:56.009
I was taking medication daily
to deal with depression and anxiety,

18:56.093 --> 18:58.303
and that made me a paranoid freak.

18:59.012 --> 19:00.889
I didn't trust a whole lot of people,

19:00.973 --> 19:04.268
and I was trying to do anything
and everything to protect a secret.

19:04.351 --> 19:05.727
I lost my mind,

19:06.436 --> 19:08.438
and I did some things,

19:08.522 --> 19:11.233
I said some things that I'm not proud of.

19:11.316 --> 19:17.197
And that's not me making excuses
for what I did, because I did fuck up.

19:17.281 --> 19:20.784
I made mistakes,
and I will take ownership in that.

19:23.078 --> 19:26.748
Was there, like, a realization
that you had, or what made you…

19:27.958 --> 19:29.793
I, like, um…

19:31.003 --> 19:35.132
-You don't have to talk about it.
-No, actually, I can. Um…

19:36.675 --> 19:39.428
I had a pretty bad weekend in LA.

19:39.511 --> 19:40.888
What do you mean?

19:40.971 --> 19:45.350
So after the breakup with Cassie,
it was… pretty rough.

19:45.434 --> 19:46.518
I hit rock bottom.

19:48.478 --> 19:50.147
I took a lot of Xanax,

19:50.230 --> 19:52.524
not thinking I was gonna wake up
the next morning.

19:52.608 --> 19:53.442
Mmm.

19:53.942 --> 19:55.068
And…

19:55.777 --> 19:56.778
I did.

20:00.324 --> 20:01.408
It was pretty bad.

20:02.784 --> 20:04.328
I literally drove home that day.

20:04.411 --> 20:06.955
I put Zuka in the car
and drove back to Colorado.

20:07.039 --> 20:09.291
And my parents… My family doesn't know.

20:13.795 --> 20:16.089
And I think that was… For me, it's like…

20:16.173 --> 20:18.217
-Yeah.
-I only have one life.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.134
Yeah.

20:19.218 --> 20:21.053
-Something's gotta change, or…
-Yeah.

20:21.136 --> 20:22.262
…I'm not gonna be here.

20:22.346 --> 20:23.263
-Yeah.
-So…

20:23.347 --> 20:25.891
-We want you here.
-I know. I wanna be here.

20:25.974 --> 20:28.685
-Ah.
-And, like, it's in the past now.

20:28.769 --> 20:29.603
Yeah.

20:31.063 --> 20:32.898
That was tough.

20:32.981 --> 20:35.150
Okay, I'm sorry,
can I give you a hug?

20:37.152 --> 20:38.278
Aw.

20:39.863 --> 20:41.823
You were there for me
with my parents' divorce,

20:41.907 --> 20:43.033
and now you're here for this.

20:43.116 --> 20:45.202
It just… It means so much, and…

20:46.078 --> 20:48.247
I'm here for you,
whatever you need.

20:48.330 --> 20:49.748
-It's gonna be a lot.
-Yeah.

20:49.831 --> 20:52.876
Just because…
I haven't told my dad yet, or Connor.

20:52.960 --> 20:54.086
-So…
-Yeah.

20:54.169 --> 20:56.672
…those are gonna be tougher conversations.

20:57.256 --> 21:01.093
My biggest fear in all this is if I have
a broken relationship with my dad, or…

21:01.176 --> 21:03.929
What's your relationship like
with him now?

21:04.012 --> 21:06.765
Him and I,
we were doing so good on our relationship.

21:06.848 --> 21:09.268
Through The Bachelor,
it made us closer, letting him in.

21:09.351 --> 21:13.272
But it was also a lot to be going through
my own personal transformations

21:13.355 --> 21:14.356
under his roof.

21:14.439 --> 21:17.359
-Yeah. Mm-hmm.
-And I've been avoiding him just because…

21:17.442 --> 21:20.195
He probably feels that,
so that's probably why.

21:20.279 --> 21:21.363
Yeah.

21:22.489 --> 21:23.490
Yeah, so…

21:23.573 --> 21:26.034
I know it's gonna be hard
to talk with your family

21:26.118 --> 21:29.204
because they are strong-willed people,

21:29.288 --> 21:32.666
but you gotta make sure
that something like this comes from you.

21:33.583 --> 21:34.584
I'm going to.

21:36.586 --> 21:38.964
And you keep your happiness top-of-mind,

21:39.047 --> 21:42.467
because I don't want
what happened in LA to happen again.

21:43.093 --> 21:44.011
I know.

21:54.021 --> 21:55.647
Uh-oh. Zuka!

21:57.024 --> 21:58.650
-Zuka!
-Get her, Bruce.

21:58.734 --> 21:59.735
That is his bone.

22:01.278 --> 22:04.364
-Will you get… Your dog's a bully.
-She took his bone.

22:04.448 --> 22:06.116
-I know, she's a little bitch.

22:06.199 --> 22:11.204
My brother, Connor, I love the dude,
but we are super competitive.

22:11.288 --> 22:13.248
-Good boy!
-Oh! Bruce won.

22:13.332 --> 22:15.167
We're not about emotions.

22:15.250 --> 22:18.503
We don't share emotions.
He didn't even cry at his wedding.

22:18.587 --> 22:22.299
I was his best man,
and I was sitting there crying for him,

22:22.382 --> 22:24.634
and he was as serious as can be.

22:25.844 --> 22:27.012
Talk to Mom today?

22:27.095 --> 22:29.389
I've not spoken to Dad or Mom.

22:29.473 --> 22:30.432
Why?

22:30.515 --> 22:33.143
I'm… gonna talk to Dad
here shortly too, though.

22:33.852 --> 22:34.686
For what?

22:35.687 --> 22:36.605
Um…

22:38.273 --> 22:39.566
About coming out.

22:45.030 --> 22:45.864
Really?

22:47.574 --> 22:49.034
-Yeah.
-Oh.

22:49.743 --> 22:50.577
All right.

22:51.578 --> 22:52.496
I still love you.

22:54.039 --> 22:55.707
I didn't see that coming, at all.

22:56.291 --> 22:57.542
Grew up Catholic.

22:58.835 --> 23:01.421
Shit, 20 years ago,
they would have killed you, almost.

23:02.381 --> 23:03.215
I know.

23:03.298 --> 23:06.301
I should go to St. Pat's
and tell Sister Mary Ann.

23:07.010 --> 23:08.470
-That's the thing.

23:08.553 --> 23:11.973
With you, like, I was hopeful
that you'd be cool with it and good--

23:12.057 --> 23:13.892
You thought I was gonna storm out of here?

23:13.975 --> 23:14.893
I didn't know.

23:14.976 --> 23:17.104
And I know we don't talk, like, emotions.

23:17.187 --> 23:21.024
-We don't get emotional with each other.
-Not at all. Have you been seeing anybody?

23:21.108 --> 23:23.777
-No. God.
-Have you told Zuka yet?

23:24.403 --> 23:26.196
-Yeah. Zuka knows.

23:26.279 --> 23:27.739
She's known for the longest.

23:27.823 --> 23:30.534
She was so positive,
and she gave me a big kiss.

23:30.617 --> 23:33.120
You're not expecting
a big kiss from me, are you?

23:35.414 --> 23:36.873
You downloaded Grindr yet?

23:37.624 --> 23:39.209
You're a little shit. Fuck you.

23:39.876 --> 23:40.877
What? I don't judge.

23:40.961 --> 23:43.296
Thank God Mom didn't ask me
that question.

23:46.133 --> 23:50.011
-Have you told anybody else?
-So I told Mom, I told Kassidy.

23:50.095 --> 23:50.929
Really?

23:51.805 --> 23:53.390
That's it. And now you.

23:53.473 --> 23:55.100
That's big news.

23:55.183 --> 23:58.437
-Now I gotta talk to Dad.
-Ah. How do you think that's gonna go?

23:59.604 --> 24:01.440
How do you think that's gonna go?

24:01.523 --> 24:03.567
-You scared?
-Yeah.

24:03.650 --> 24:05.235
The hard part about all of this

24:05.318 --> 24:08.655
is I've never envisioned myself
having these conversations.

24:08.738 --> 24:10.949
And when I do, it sucks.

24:11.032 --> 24:14.119
My brother didn't have to come out
as straight to my parents.

24:14.202 --> 24:17.789
He didn't have to explain to people
why he was getting married to a woman.

24:17.873 --> 24:20.333
I don't want to keep having
these conversations,

24:20.417 --> 24:23.920
and I know the more I do it, the more
comfortable I'm gonna get with it,

24:24.004 --> 24:26.298
but I'm scared as hell to tell my dad.

24:26.923 --> 24:29.050
You care too much
about what people think about you.

24:30.010 --> 24:31.011
You just gotta live.

24:31.595 --> 24:33.638
Never a better time to start
than right now, right?

24:33.722 --> 24:34.681
Yeah.

24:51.198 --> 24:54.701
I don't think in the past few years
there's been a day that has gone by

24:54.784 --> 24:56.328
without me calling my dad.

24:56.411 --> 24:59.748
But there's a lot
that has not been said recently,

24:59.831 --> 25:02.918
and that's not how me
and my father have always been.

25:06.963 --> 25:07.881
What's up?

25:07.964 --> 25:09.132
Ready?

25:09.216 --> 25:10.467
What are you wearing?

25:10.967 --> 25:13.136
White tennis shoes
to go fishing in the mud.

25:13.220 --> 25:15.222
Bruh,
I'm just about to look good.

25:15.305 --> 25:16.932
-Right.

25:17.015 --> 25:20.727
'Cause the fish care about that.
Hell, there's dog hair everywhere in here.

25:22.020 --> 25:24.272
I think, looking back
at where I've come from,

25:24.356 --> 25:26.358
all of my family and friendships

25:26.983 --> 25:29.361
and the situations that I grew up in

25:29.444 --> 25:34.658
have never allowed me the safety
or the space that I need to come out.

25:35.659 --> 25:38.078
I remember my decision to leave LA,

25:38.161 --> 25:41.790
and my dad was the first person
to step up and have my back.

25:41.873 --> 25:45.335
I also remember having
a conversation with my dad

25:45.418 --> 25:49.798
in which he sat me down and just said,
"If I'm gonna do this and be here for you,

25:49.881 --> 25:51.132
I need to know everything."

25:51.216 --> 25:54.511
And even by him
going out of his way to say that,

25:54.594 --> 25:56.763
I still didn't have
the courage to tell him.

25:58.098 --> 26:00.559
We ain't the only dumbasses
trying to fish in this weather.

26:00.642 --> 26:03.186
No, the breeze
is gonna be tough with this now.

26:04.729 --> 26:06.773
I always put
a lot of pressure on myself

26:06.856 --> 26:09.609
to live up
to the expectation of my father,

26:10.902 --> 26:13.405
follow in his footsteps and make him proud

26:13.488 --> 26:16.241
and… play football
where my dad played football.

26:16.324 --> 26:19.286
Just really try to build
this legacy of our family.

26:19.786 --> 26:22.831
I always want his approval.
I always want him to love me.

26:22.914 --> 26:24.749
I always want him to be proud of me,

26:24.833 --> 26:26.751
and I never want to let him down.

26:26.835 --> 26:27.669
So…

26:29.254 --> 26:30.088
That's my dad.

26:30.589 --> 26:33.967
-What are you doing tonight?
-Uh, I don't know yet.

26:34.718 --> 26:37.512
